  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "3 digit no unit digit, ten digit and hundred digit their ratio 3:5:7 if the difference of original number and \u0155eversing the digit is 396 find the no?",
  "response": "Let the three-digit number be represented as \\( xyz \\), where \\( x \\) is the hundred's digit, \\( y \\) is the ten's digit, and \\( z \\) is the unit's digit. According to the given ratio of the digits, we can express \\( x \\), \\( y \\), and \\( z \\) in terms of a common variable \\( k \\):\n\n- \\( x = 3k \\) (hundreds digit)\n- \\( y = 5k \\) (tens digit)\n- \\( z = 7k \\) (units digit)\n\nThe number can be expressed as:\n\n\\[\nN = 100x + 10y + z = 100(3k) + 10(5k) + (7k) = 300k + 50k + 7k = 357k\n\\]\n\nWhen the digits are reversed, the number becomes \\( zyx \\):\n\n\\[\nzyx = 100z + 10y + x = 100(7k) + 10(5k) + (3k) = 700k + 50k + 3k = 753k\n\\]\n\nThe difference between the original number and the reversed number is given as:\n\n\\[\nN - zyx = 357k - 753k = -396\n\\]\n\nSimplifying the expression:\n\n\\[\n-396 = -396k\n\\]\n\nThus, we can set up the equation:\n\n\\[\n357k - 753k = -396\n\\]\n\nThis simplifies to:\n\n\\[\n-396k = -396\n\\]\n\nDividing both sides by \\(-396\\) gives:\n\n\\[\nk = 1\n\\]\n\nNow, substituting \\( k = 1 \\) back into the expressions for \\( x, y, \\) and \\( z \\):\n\n- \\( x = 3(1) = 3 \\)\n- \\( y = 5(1) = 5 \\)\n- \\( z = 7(1) = 7 \\)\n\nThus, the three-digit number is:\n\n\\[\nN = 357\n\\]\n\nFinally, let's verify if the difference between the number and its reverse equals 396:\n\n- The reverse of 357 is 753.\n- The difference is \\( 753 - 357 = 396 \\).\n\nTherefore, the number is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{357}\n\\]",
